    Date: Thu 9 Apr 87 07:07:14-EST
    From: Dennis G. Perry &lt;PERRY@vax.darpa.mil&gt;

    Jon, what if someone in the UK named their machine "EDU.ISI.UK"?
    Are reversed names confusing, especially since the European standard is
    to reverse the ordering of the name.

Please choose your words carefully.  In my opinion, it is the domain
system that does it in reverse and the UK that does it in the right
order.  Anyway, as SRA pointed out explicit routing would resolve
ambiguities as well as confusion.

